==Viking bed burials== In several [[Viking]] [[ship burial]]s from [[Norway]] and [[Sweden]], including the [[Oseberg ship|Oseberg ship burial]] (dated to 834) and [[Gokstad ship|Gokstad ship burial]] (dated to the late 9th century), the deceased had been laid out on beds. However, true bed burials, in which the bed is buried directly in the ground are not known.<ref>{{harvnb|Gjerset|1969|p=34}}</ref><ref>{{harvnb|Scragg|2003|p=40}}</ref>
