{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}} {{Use British English|date=May 2016}} {{Infobox football biography | name = John Ackroyd | image = | fullname = John William Ackroyd | birth_date = 1895 | birth_place = [[Rotherham]], England | death_date = | death_place = | position = Defender | years1 = | clubs1=[[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]] | caps1= | goals1 = | years2 = 1919 | clubs2=[[Rotherham County F.C.|Rotherham County]] | caps2=1 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = | clubs3=[[Scunthorpe United F.C.|Scunthorpe & Lindsey United]]| caps3= | goals3 = | years4 = 1922−1923 | clubs4=[[Exeter City F.C.|Exeter City]]| caps4=30 | goals4 = 0 | years5 = 1923− | clubs5=[[Grimsby Town F.C.|Grimsby Town]]| caps5=6 | goals5 = 0 }} '''John William "Jack"<ref name=stfc/> Ackroyd''' (1895–unknown) was an English [[association football|footballer]] who played in [[the Football League]] for [[Exeter City F.C.|Exeter City]],<ref name=stfc/> [[Grimsby Town F.C.|Grimsby Town]] and [[Rotherham County F.C.|Rotherham County]]. He also played for [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]] and [[Scunthorpe United F.C.|Scunthorpe & Lindsey United]]. He was born in [[Rotherham]], England.<ref>*Joyce, Michael: "The Football League player's records 1888 to 1939 " ({{ISBN|1899468676}}).</ref>
