{{Infobox boxer | name=Jundy Maraon | nationality={{flagicon|Philippines}} [[Filipino people|Filipino]] | realname=Jundy Maraon | image= | nickname=Pretty Boy | height={{height|ft=5|in=6}} | weight=[[Bantamweight]] | birth_date={{Birth date and age|1985|2|25|df=y}} | birth_place=[[Philippines]] | style=[[Southpaw (boxing)|Southpaw]] | total=17 | wins=15 | KO=11 | losses=1 | draws=1 }}
'''Jundy Maraon''' (born 25 February 1985) also known as "[[batang gwaping]]" is a [[Philippines|Filipino]] professional [[Boxing|boxer]].
He was WBO Asia Pacific bantamweight champion and resides in [[Blancia St. Molave]], [[Zamboanga del Sur]]. He's married to Naomie Maraon in Talisay City, Cebu last June 9, 2011.
== Boxing career == Maraon made his professional debut on 26 July 2003, defeating Rogelio Oro at [[Ipil, Zamboanga Sibugay]], Philippines.
