== Monochorionic twin pregnancy complication == {{Empty section|date=March 2018}} <ref name="elsevier47"/><ref name="wkhealth753"/><ref name="elsevier514"/><ref name="karger181"/><ref name="karger181"/><ref name="elsevier796"/><ref name="elsevier417"/>
== Diagnosis and staging == [[File:Middle cerebral artery peak systolic velocity in TAPS.jpg|thumb|right|Diagnosis by doppler ultrasound measurement of the Middle Cerebral Artery - Peak Systolic Velocity (MCA-PSV)]] Different stages of TAPS are identified using the criteria as shown in the following tables.<ref name="karger181"/>
=== Postnatal classification=== {| style="width: 400px;" class="wikitable" |- ! Postnatal stage !! Intertwin hemoglobin difference (g/dL) |- | Stage 1 || >8.0 g/dL |- | Stage 2|| >11.0 g/dL |- | Stage 3|| >14.0 g/dL |- | Stage 4 || >17.0 g/dL |- | Stage 5|| >20.0 g/dL |}
== Treatment == <ref name="karger181"/><ref name="elsevier2008"/><ref name="wiley592"/><ref name="elsevier209"/><ref name="wiley490"/><ref>{{Cite journal|title = Management of Twin Anemia-Polycythemia Sequence Using Intrauterine Blood Transfusion for the Donor and Partial Exchange Transfusion for the Recipient|url = http://www.karger.com?doi=10.1159/000346413|journal = Fetal Diagnosis and Therapy|pages = 121–126|volume = 34|issue = 2|doi = 10.1159/000346413|pmid = 23713060|first = L.|last = Genova|first2 = F.|last2 = Slaghekke|first3 = F.J.|last3 = Klumper|first4 = J.M.|last4 = Middeldorp|first5 = S.J.|last5 = Steggerda|first6 = D.|last6 = Oepkes|first7 = E.|last7 = Lopriore|year = 2013}}</ref>
The use of the so-called Solomon technique or dichorionization in fetoscopic laser therapy for TTTS is proven to be beneficial in preventing post-laser TAPS.{{Citation needed|date = December 2015}} With this technique, not only all anastomoses are coagulated but also a line is drawn between those in order to coagulate anastomoses that might not (yet) be visible during fetoscopy.{{Citation needed|date = December 2015}} It should be stressed that the success of such a technique is highly dependent on the specific situation.{{Citation needed|date = December 2015}} For example, when one of the fetusses obstructs the view on the vascular equator (the part of the placenta where the anastomoses need to be coagulated), complete dichorionization by the Solomon technique might not be possible.{{Citation needed|date = December 2015}}
=== Perinatal outcome === {{Empty section|date=March 2018}} <ref name="karger181"/><ref>{{Cite journal|title = Severe cerebral injury in a recipient with twin anemia–polycythemia sequence|url = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/uog.12337/abstract|journal = Ultrasound in Obstetrics & Gynecology|date = 2013-06-01|issn = 1469-0705|pages = 702–706|volume = 41|issue = 6|doi = 10.1002/uog.12337|language = en|first = E.|last = Lopriore|first2 = F.|last2 = Slaghekke|first3 = K. J.|last3 = Kersbergen|first4 = L. S.|last4 = de Vries|first5 = A. P.|last5 = Drogtrop|first6 = J. M.|last6 = Middeldorp|first7 = D.|last7 = Oepkes|first8 = M. J.|last8 = Benders}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title = Fetal brain lesion associated with spontaneous twin anemia–polycythemia sequence|url = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/uog.12574/abstract|journal = Ultrasound in Obstetrics & Gynecology|date = 2013-12-01|issn = 1469-0705|pages = 721–722|volume = 42|issue = 6|doi = 10.1002/uog.12574|language = en|first = D.|last = Luminoso|first2 = C. O.|last2 = Figueira|first3 = M.|last3 = Marins|first4 = C. F. A.|last4 = Peralta}}</ref>
